---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import BiocareValues from '../components/BiocareValues.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About Us" description="St. John Biocare is a SEC-registered foundation born from one family's experience of kidney failure — our story, mission, values and leadership." image="/images/og/og-about.jpg">
  <PageHero
    image="/images/heroes/about-hero.webp"
    alt="An adult son resting a reassuring hand on his elderly father's shoulder, both smiling"
    eyebrow="Our story"
    title="A foundation, born from a real family story."
    subtitle="Not a corporate chain, but a foundation — born from one son's love for his mother, and a refusal to let excellent dialysis be a privilege of the few."
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:760px" class:list={['stack']}>
      <p>
        It began the way so many important things do — in a family, in a hard season. A son
        watched his mother face end-stage renal disease and walked every step of it beside her:
        the hospital, the fear, the slow new rhythm of dialysis that would now shape her weeks.
        Somewhere along the way he saw something he would never forget — just how much truly
        <em>excellent</em> care can change, not only for the patient in the chair, but for the
        whole family holding its breath around her.
      </p>
      <p>
        He also saw how rare that kind of care could be. When his mother moved to outpatient
        dialysis, what the family found at existing free-standing centers convinced him there
        had to be a better alternative — one built around the patient, not the margin. The idea
        sprouted from something simple and stubborn: compassion, and an unwavering grit for
        excellence. Together with a lifelong friend and partner, he set out to build it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Their conviction was that the highest quality of hemodialysis should never be a privilege
        of the few. It should reach the masses — ordinary Filipino families — without ever asking
        them to trade their safety for what they can afford. That belief is still the engine of
        everything we do.
      </p>
      <p>
        St. John Biocare was registered with the SEC on <strong>June 28, 2011</strong>, and opened
        its first clinic in Quezon City on <strong>October 16, 2011</strong>. We were built as a
        non-stock <strong>foundation</strong> on purpose: it means we answer to a mission, not to
        shareholders — which is why we can lead with the patient, and truly mean it.
      </p>

      <div class="notice">
        <strong>Our care philosophy</strong>
        <p style="margin:.4rem 0 0">
          “The St. John Biocare Way is to put the patient first… we must see the world through
          the eyes of our patients and their families.” We call the people we serve
          <strong>client-patients</strong>. And we hold to one line: <em>Dedicated to all of us.</em>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--sand">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">
      <div class="grid grid--2">
        <div class="card">
          <h2 style="font-size:1.35rem">Our vision</h2>
          <p><em>“To become the leading free-standing dialysis center and diagnostic facility
          in providing exemplary service to patients with end-stage renal disease.”</em></p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h2 style="font-size:1.35rem">Our mission</h2>
          <p><em>“To provide the best-quality expert clinical care through state-of-the-art,
          innovative and affordable hemodialysis treatments and diagnostics manned by
          outstanding and compassionate personnel, responsive to the needs of our patients.”</em></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="center" style="margin-bottom:30px">
        <p class="eyebrow">What we stand for</p>
        <h2>The BIOCARE values.</h2>
      </div>
      <BiocareValues />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--forest">
    <div class="container center" style="max-width:760px">
      <p class="eyebrow">More than procedures</p>
      <h2>We build patient communities.</h2>
      <p style="color:#e5f3e9;font-size:1.15rem">
        At St. John Biocare, we don't just perform procedures — we <strong>build and espouse patient
        communities</strong>. Dialysis is a shared journey, so we bring patients, families and staff
        together to support one another, learn, and find strength in good company. Here, you are never
        just a case — you belong.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
